1
00:00:00,667 --> 00:00:02,767
<i> Bro, I saw Jade with Edward.</i>

2
00:00:02,767 --> 00:00:04,600
<i> Yeah, well, they're close.</i>

3
00:00:04,933 --> 00:00:06,100
<i> Bro, it's different this time.</i>

4
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:07,633
<i> They're really close.</i>

5
00:00:07,633 --> 00:00:09,667
<i> They're almost
kissing each other.</i>

6
00:00:09,667 --> 00:00:11,833
<i> - We had a moment...
</i>- [SHRIEKING]

7
00:00:11,833 --> 00:00:13,100
[COUGHING]

8
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:14,933
<i> You kissed?!</i>

9
00:00:15,133 --> 00:00:16,467
<i> Kiss... no!</i>

10
00:00:16,467 --> 00:00:19,000
<i>Ladies and gentlemen
and everything in between,</i>

11
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,600
<i> we have a situationship.</i>

12
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:22,733
<i> How about his girlfriend?
Is she here?</i>

13
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:25,267
<i>Sari is Martin's executive
assistant.</i>

14
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:26,767
<i> Not his girlfriend.</i>

15
00:00:26,767 --> 00:00:28,100
<i> What?</i>

16
00:00:29,467 --> 00:00:31,000
<i>You said that Andy Arellano
sent one of his men</i>

17
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,133
<i> to beat you up.</i>

18
00:00:32,133 --> 00:00:33,567
<i> You mean to tell me...</i>

19
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,467
<i>he has something to do
with this?</i>

20
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:38,000
<i>If Uncle Andy is somehow
connected with Sandro,</i>

21
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,000
<i>it's not impossible
that he has something to do</i>

22
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,600
<i> with the death of my dad
and your father</i>

23
00:00:43,933 --> 00:00:46,100
<i> just to acquire Hotel 88.</i>

24
00:00:48,267 --> 00:00:49,833
So are you Martin's girlfriend?

25
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:52,967
I told you I'm not!
I just pretended to be!

26
00:00:52,967 --> 00:00:54,267
Because?

27
00:00:54,267 --> 00:00:55,633
Because Uncle Ronald
wanted to see

28
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:56,900
that Martin is committed!

29
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:59,600
- For what?
- [SARI GROANING]

30
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:01,833
[STUTTERING] He said
it reflects how--

31
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:04,533
how committed he is
to the business!

32
00:01:04,533 --> 00:01:05,600
Okay, and then?

33
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:08,133
That's all there is to it!

34
00:01:08,167 --> 00:01:10,300
He believes in a lot of...

35
00:01:10,667 --> 00:01:11,833
Ugh, enough!

36
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:14,667
- [SARI CLICKS TONGUE]
- Wa-- wait, Sari.

37
00:01:14,667 --> 00:01:15,800
Just wait, because...

38
00:01:17,033 --> 00:01:18,267
I'm so lost.

39
00:01:18,667 --> 00:01:20,300
So, you're saying that you
pretended

40
00:01:20,300 --> 00:01:21,700
to be in a relationship
with Martin...

41
00:01:22,133 --> 00:01:25,100
to be able to convince
an investor, is that it?

42
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,300
Yeah, kind of... yeah!

43
00:01:29,867 --> 00:01:31,167
Enough of this!

44
00:01:31,167 --> 00:01:32,633
Just stay here, okay?

45
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:33,967
I'll tell you
all about it later!

46
00:01:33,967 --> 00:01:35,533
Just where did he go?

47
00:01:35,533 --> 00:01:37,033
Maybe he's waiting for a boat.

48
00:01:37,033 --> 00:01:43,967
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

49
00:01:51,233 --> 00:01:58,167
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

50
00:02:53,933 --> 00:03:00,867
[PHONE VIBRATING]

51
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:03,933
Martin.

52
00:03:03,933 --> 00:03:09,233
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

53
00:03:09,633 --> 00:03:10,633
No.

54
00:03:10,633 --> 00:03:12,767
We can't let Andy
become a business partner.

55
00:03:12,767 --> 00:03:14,400
It would be safer for all of
us that way.

56
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:16,133
Yes.

57
00:03:16,933 --> 00:03:18,433
I confronted Uncle Andy.

58
00:03:18,433 --> 00:03:19,900
But he just denied it.

59
00:03:20,933 --> 00:03:22,167
But I know, Martin.

60
00:03:22,867 --> 00:03:24,700
I know he's hiding something.

61
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:26,067
But what about that Sandro?

62
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:27,967
What happened to him?

63
00:03:27,967 --> 00:03:29,033
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

64
00:03:29,033 --> 00:03:30,267
I don't know.

65
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,067
All Dad said was that he's
taking care of it.

66
00:03:33,967 --> 00:03:35,300
Maybe they buried the body.

67
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:37,167
I don't know.

68
00:03:37,933 --> 00:03:38,933
Martin.

69
00:03:40,267 --> 00:03:42,267
You will tell no one.

70
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:45,767
Not a single soul.

71
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:48,400
I know.

72
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,733
Promise me.

73
00:03:52,433 --> 00:03:54,000
Neither my siblings...

74
00:03:55,033 --> 00:03:56,467
nor yours.

75
00:03:58,033 --> 00:03:59,800
They can't know about this.

76
00:04:00,033 --> 00:04:01,133
Alright.

77
00:04:01,467 --> 00:04:02,667
I get it.

78
00:04:03,733 --> 00:04:04,733
Our focus right now

79
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:07,200
is for Andy not to be
a part of the hotel.

80
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:10,367
It's the only way
to protect our families.

81
00:04:10,367 --> 00:04:16,167
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES,
FADES]

82
00:04:16,167 --> 00:04:19,200
- [ANDY GRUNTS]
- [JUAN SCREAMING IN PAIN]

83
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:22,167
[GRUNTS, PANTING]

84
00:04:22,167 --> 00:04:24,167
I don't know where Father is.

85
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:27,300
I don't have a single clue
about the treasure

86
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:28,767
you're talking about.

87
00:04:29,733 --> 00:04:32,067
I'll say it to you over
and over again.

88
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,333
Where's the map?

89
00:04:35,067 --> 00:04:36,500
I need a map.

90
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:41,067
I told you, I don't where
the treasure is!

91
00:04:41,267 --> 00:04:43,233
Now you're asking me
for a map too?

92
00:04:43,233 --> 00:04:44,400
- [BANGS]
- [YELPS IN FEAR]

93
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:46,333
Why are you lying to me?!

94
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:47,500
Huh?!

95
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:50,200
Your father has been missing
for a while now.

96
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:52,233
Why are you only
looking for him now? Huh?!

97
00:04:53,233 --> 00:04:57,467
Because he is not why you came
here at Isla Solara.

98
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:00,300
But don't worry.

99
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:02,867
I'm not gonna kill you.

100
00:05:03,567 --> 00:05:06,000
I'm just going to prolong
your suffering

101
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:08,433
until you finally give me
what I need.

102
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:11,267
Where's the map?!

103
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:16,900
[PHONE RINGING]

104
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:17,933
[PHONE BEEPS]

105
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:21,367
[SCOFFS]

106
00:05:24,467 --> 00:05:26,867
You're not even answering
Luna's calls.

107
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,733
What more mine?

108
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,500
As usual.

109
00:05:32,233 --> 00:05:33,500
I'm being ignored.

110
00:05:36,267 --> 00:05:38,233
I'm genuinely concerned
for him.

111
00:05:39,233 --> 00:05:41,267
That's why I'm doing
everything I'm doing right now.

112
00:05:43,233 --> 00:05:44,467
Just like how I worried
about Jade

113
00:05:44,467 --> 00:05:45,867
when Roy took her.

114
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:48,367
But what can I do?

115
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,400
[CHUCKLES]

116
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,867
- Why can't I accept--
- [TRIXIE] Justin?

117
00:05:55,933 --> 00:05:56,933
Sorry.

118
00:05:58,100 --> 00:05:59,367
I thought you were Cheska.

119
00:05:59,967 --> 00:06:01,267
You shouldn't have heard that.

120
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:03,100
No, don't apologize.

121
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:05,133
I should've said it was me.

122
00:06:07,967 --> 00:06:10,000
Do you want to be alone?
I can go.

123
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,567
- I'll come back later.
- No, no, no.

124
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:14,300
Stay.

125
00:06:16,967 --> 00:06:18,067
Um...

126
00:06:18,467 --> 00:06:20,167
Are you done venting?

127
00:06:20,833 --> 00:06:21,833
Yes.

128
00:06:23,033 --> 00:06:24,500
I just want you to be here.

129
00:06:26,433 --> 00:06:27,600
Okay.

130
00:06:28,167 --> 00:06:35,100
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

131
00:06:45,167 --> 00:06:47,033
I'll give Uncle Ronald
the contract.

132
00:06:47,033 --> 00:06:48,500
I'll deal with Luna later.

133
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:52,033
I'll find more information
about Mister Andy.

134
00:06:52,033 --> 00:06:56,167
I'll find out his role
in our fathers' death.

135
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:57,333
Yes, do that.

136
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:59,867
Even if he doesn't
become a partner,

137
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:03,033
as long as he's interested,
he won't back off.

138
00:07:06,167 --> 00:07:07,833
We're all in danger.

139
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,533
We need to outsmart him.

140
00:07:11,133 --> 00:07:16,033
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYS]

141
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,467
What is it?

142
00:07:18,933 --> 00:07:19,967
Leon.

143
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:23,067
I think...

144
00:07:24,533 --> 00:07:26,300
I think there's something more.

145
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,467
[GROANS]

146
00:07:31,367 --> 00:07:34,167
[LEON] About the same time
I had Sandro's phone,

147
00:07:34,533 --> 00:07:37,400
some men beat me up,
then ransacked my car.

148
00:07:39,267 --> 00:07:41,000
[MARTIN]
They wanted something from you?

149
00:07:42,033 --> 00:07:43,300
[LEON] Yes.

150
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:46,500
They just don't want to be
a part of the hotel.

151
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:49,500
They want to find
or get something from me.

152
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:53,367
It must be something valuable.

153
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:56,067
How can you say that?

154
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,500
Look at me.

155
00:07:58,733 --> 00:08:00,533
They wouldn't beat me up

156
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:03,567
then rummage through my stuff

157
00:08:03,967 --> 00:08:05,667
for something
that isn't valuable.

158
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:11,433
You're right. But wait...

159
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:15,433
Papa left us a video message.

160
00:08:16,233 --> 00:08:18,533
He said... What was it?

161
00:08:22,733 --> 00:08:24,433
He said not to sell
the hotel off,

162
00:08:24,433 --> 00:08:26,633
because there's something
important in there.

163
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:29,733
Then? What else?

164
00:08:29,733 --> 00:08:31,700
Well, the video was cut short.

165
00:08:32,133 --> 00:08:34,067
Whatever they're looking for,

166
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,633
they thought I had it.

167
00:08:37,633 --> 00:08:41,733
Or that
it's in the hotel itself.

168
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,367
That's why
Andy is so interested in it!

169
00:08:47,967 --> 00:08:54,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS]

170
00:09:00,367 --> 00:09:02,967
I'll look through
my dad's stuff.

171
00:09:02,967 --> 00:09:04,333
Okay?

172
00:09:04,333 --> 00:09:05,333
Alright.

173
00:09:05,333 --> 00:09:06,667
Bro, be careful.

174
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:09,600
You might get stopped again.

175
00:09:11,267 --> 00:09:12,833
Martin!

176
00:09:13,933 --> 00:09:15,333
Be careful, too.

177
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:22,267
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

178
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:28,267
I'm leaving!
No matter what you do...

179
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:31,000
- I won't change my mind!
- Uncle Ron...

180
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,733
Don't you dare call me uncle!

181
00:09:33,733 --> 00:09:37,267
I agreed because I thought
you could be trusted!

182
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:41,033
Sir! Sir! Please, I'm sorry!

183
00:09:41,033 --> 00:09:44,033
I'm sorry, but Sir Martin
can be trusted.

184
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,200
He just really wanted
to please you.

185
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:48,633
That's why he did it!

186
00:09:48,633 --> 00:09:49,867
Enough, Sari!

187
00:09:50,733 --> 00:09:53,333
I wouldn't listen
to someone like you.

188
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:57,667
Besides being
just an assistant...

189
00:09:57,667 --> 00:09:59,200
you're also a scammer.

190
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:02,167
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

191
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:05,100
Sir! Sir, please! Sir, please!

192
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:07,833
[CRYING]
Just get mad at me, please!

193
00:10:09,067 --> 00:10:11,133
Please, just get mad at me!

194
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:15,267
Not at Sir Martin.

195
00:10:15,267 --> 00:10:18,733
- Please give him a chance!
- No!

196
00:10:18,733 --> 00:10:21,100
- No, Sari!
- Please, sir!

197
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:23,333
Those who do business
with me know very well

198
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:26,133
that I place a high value
on trust.

199
00:10:27,867 --> 00:10:29,800
And you've ruined it!

200
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:32,933
[CRYING] Sir, please!

201
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:36,167
So don't expect
anything from me.

202
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,700
Sir!

203
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:39,800
Sir, please.

204
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,367
Sari, move!

205
00:10:41,367 --> 00:10:42,733
I don't want to hurt you.

206
00:10:43,933 --> 00:10:46,233
- Sir, please.
- Oh, for goodness sake.

207
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:49,433
Sir, please! Please! Sir!

208
00:10:49,433 --> 00:10:52,733
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

209
00:10:52,733 --> 00:10:53,767
Sir...

210
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:59,400
[CRYING] Sir Martin,
where are you?

211
00:11:03,133 --> 00:11:04,433
[PHONE BEEPS]

212
00:11:04,433 --> 00:11:10,433
"Martin: Gio, Kiko, don't leave
the hotel. We need to talk."

213
00:11:10,467 --> 00:11:13,967
"Where's Leon? Is he okay?"

214
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:22,400
"He's fine. But we need
to have a family meeting."

215
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:26,400
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

216
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,767
[JADE] Kiko.

217
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:32,233
Martin has also spoken
to his brother Leo.

218
00:11:32,233 --> 00:11:33,833
Where's my brother?

219
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:35,833
How is he?

220
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:38,267
He just said that he's fine.

221
00:11:38,267 --> 00:11:40,833
And that we have
a family meeting later.

222
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:44,400
Why is he talking to Martin
and not us?

223
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:47,500
Jade.

224
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:49,433
I already talked to Leon.

225
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:51,500
He said he was fine,
but we need to talk.

226
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,500
Are you talking to him, too?

227
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:58,500
Martin and Leon are talking.

228
00:11:59,267 --> 00:12:01,267
Are they together now?

229
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:03,800
I wonder what's going on.

230
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:08,300
[CHESKA]
Hey! You can't go alone!

231
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:10,167
[JUSTIN]
Keep your voice down!

232
00:12:10,167 --> 00:12:11,967
We're planning, aren't we?

233
00:12:11,967 --> 00:12:15,167
Planning? You're the only one
who makes the plan.

234
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:18,967
You'll also be there.
As my lookout.

235
00:12:18,967 --> 00:12:22,267
Okay, but how will we know
if you need help?

236
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:26,500
I've thought about that.

237
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:28,400
I know someone who will
give us comms

238
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:31,467
so that we can hear
each other.

239
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:34,500
Well, I'm not surprised
you have friends like that.

240
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,967
[CHUCKLES]
I'm an Almazan, Cheska.

241
00:12:36,967 --> 00:12:38,400
You know, I am the man.

242
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:41,333
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

243
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:42,833
Hey, the man.

244
00:12:42,833 --> 00:12:44,433
Answer the call.

245
00:12:46,033 --> 00:12:47,800
The man... [LAUGHS]

246
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:52,067
Luna?

247
00:12:52,067 --> 00:12:55,100
[LUNA]<i> I talked to Martin.
</i> He told us to go home.

248
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:56,900
Is he okay?

249
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:02,100
Yes, there is an emergency.
Go home.

250
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:03,233
<i> Now?</i>

251
00:13:03,233 --> 00:13:05,500
Yes! Hurry up, Justin.

252
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:10,567
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:13:10,567 --> 00:13:13,400
Leon's home. They're asking
for a family meeting.

254
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,333
Go. That's important.

255
00:13:16,333 --> 00:13:18,400
Family meetings
are important, right?

256
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:21,933
Yes, we do that, too!

257
00:13:21,967 --> 00:13:24,067
But we're not done
with this yet.

258
00:13:24,067 --> 00:13:26,133
Justin, that's important.

259
00:13:26,133 --> 00:13:28,267
You know that, too. Go ahead.

260
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:33,267
Hey, wait! This isn't paid yet!

261
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:40,567
[JUSTIN] Oh! Leon's here!

262
00:13:40,567 --> 00:13:43,100
[JADE] Oh my god! Leon!

263
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:47,367
Leon, what happened to you?
Does it hurt?

264
00:13:47,367 --> 00:13:50,633
- I'll call Dr. Tenorio!
- Leon, what happened?

265
00:13:50,633 --> 00:13:52,433
What do you mean
you don't need one?

266
00:13:52,433 --> 00:13:54,367
You don't look okay!

267
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:57,000
Look at yourself.
You have a lot of injuries.

268
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,433
Leon, let's go to the hospital
right now!

269
00:13:59,433 --> 00:14:01,100
What happened to you, Leon?

270
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:03,367
What the...
Who did this to you?

271
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:08,500
[GIO] What are we looking for?
The videos Dad mentioned?

272
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:10,500
He never said anything, right?

273
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:12,100
He told us not
to sell the hotel

274
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:13,967
because there's something
important here.

275
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:18,400
Wasn't he just
being sentimental?

276
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:21,333
I thought he meant family,
friendship, and unity.

277
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:24,333
- Those things.
- Something physical, Gio.

278
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:26,667
Just check his stuff!

279
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:29,667
Documents, files, whatever.

280
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:32,000
Why are you suddenly interested
with Dad's video?

281
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,700
[MARTIN]
I'll tell you next time.

282
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:36,700
All I'm asking is
for you to search.

283
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:39,200
You could even ask Raphie
for help.

284
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:42,233
I'll help you once I talk
to Uncle Ronald.

285
00:14:43,167 --> 00:14:44,500
- Uh...
- [MARTIN] That's final.

286
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:47,367
He will be our partner.

287
00:14:47,367 --> 00:14:49,333
You're being bossy again.

288
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:50,700
What about Luna's hard work?

289
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:55,167
I didn't choose Uncle Ronald
to disregard Luna.

290
00:14:55,167 --> 00:14:57,367
I am not being selfish.

291
00:14:57,367 --> 00:14:59,600
Do you think I would
believe that?

292
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,133
You think I don't notice

293
00:15:01,133 --> 00:15:03,933
how you're always
taking Luna's side lately?

294
00:15:03,967 --> 00:15:05,967
Who's being selfish now?

295
00:15:07,467 --> 00:15:09,633
W-wait. Hold on.

296
00:15:10,667 --> 00:15:12,500
Martin.

297
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,967
I think you might have
a problem with Sir Ronald.

298
00:15:14,967 --> 00:15:18,167
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

299
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:20,000
What problem?

300
00:15:21,667 --> 00:15:23,367
He found out the truth.

301
00:15:24,567 --> 00:15:26,567
That Sari isn't
your girlfriend.

302
00:15:26,567 --> 00:15:33,467
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

303
00:15:39,733 --> 00:15:41,367
That thief messed with me.

304
00:15:41,933 --> 00:15:43,200
I've already been checked

305
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,267
and I've reported the incident
to the police,

306
00:15:44,267 --> 00:15:45,900
so you have
nothing to worry about.

307
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:47,400
Leon!

308
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:50,900
What we need to talk about
is Uncle Andy.

309
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:53,533
You still want to talk business
after getting beaten up?

310
00:15:53,533 --> 00:15:55,500
This is important, Justin.

311
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:56,367
I already told Martin that

312
00:15:56,367 --> 00:15:58,567
Uncle Ronald
would be our partner.

313
00:15:58,567 --> 00:15:59,633
What?!

314
00:16:01,267 --> 00:16:04,033
L-Leon,
we chose Uncle Andy.

315
00:16:04,033 --> 00:16:06,533
Did you let your friend
trick you, Leon?

316
00:16:06,533 --> 00:16:08,500
We're choosing Uncle Andy,

317
00:16:08,533 --> 00:16:09,933
and that's final!

318
00:16:09,933 --> 00:16:14,933
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

319
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:17,600
You have to trust me on this.

320
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:20,433
I am doing this
for our family.

321
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:24,767
Leon... Leon, you need
to see a doctor!

322
00:16:24,767 --> 00:16:26,033
No!

323
00:16:26,033 --> 00:16:31,733
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

324
00:16:31,733 --> 00:16:34,733
I should've been there
when he arrived, sir.

325
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:36,667
I knew he was coming.

326
00:16:37,733 --> 00:16:41,267
But Sir Kiko entertained
Sir Ronald.

327
00:16:42,733 --> 00:16:46,767
It's not their fault
the truth slipped out.

328
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:50,000
What did you do?

329
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,833
I went after him.

330
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:53,667
I tried to stop him, sir.

331
00:16:53,667 --> 00:16:56,033
I begged him.

332
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:59,400
I apologized as well.

333
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,000
[MARTIN SIGHS]

334
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,633
What did Uncle Ronald say?

335
00:17:04,467 --> 00:17:05,733
He said...

336
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:09,633
"Those who do business with me

337
00:17:09,633 --> 00:17:12,867
know that I place
the highest value on trust."

338
00:17:19,667 --> 00:17:21,500
"And you ruined my trust."

339
00:17:23,767 --> 00:17:26,133
"You won't be getting anything
from me anymore."

340
00:17:30,833 --> 00:17:31,833
[SIGHS]

341
00:17:32,667 --> 00:17:33,633
Sir.

342
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:35,433
I'm sorry.

343
00:17:37,133 --> 00:17:38,767
Sir Martin, please.

344
00:17:40,933 --> 00:17:43,667
Sir Martin, please.
I'm sorry, sir.

345
00:17:43,667 --> 00:17:44,800
Sir.

346
00:17:46,967 --> 00:17:48,933
Sir, I'm sorry.

347
00:17:50,567 --> 00:17:54,800
[SOBS] I'm sorry
I failed to do my job.

348
00:17:54,800 --> 00:18:01,700
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

349
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:07,667
[SNIFFLES, SOBS]

350
00:18:07,667 --> 00:18:08,767
Sir.

351
00:18:09,733 --> 00:18:11,500
Don't say sorry.

352
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,833
[SOBS] Sir...

353
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:19,567
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

354
00:18:19,567 --> 00:18:20,933
It's not your fault.

355
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:23,900
You were just doing your job.

356
00:18:25,533 --> 00:18:27,400
- Sir...
- Okay?

357
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,867
Hey, that's enough.

358
00:18:32,733 --> 00:18:34,033
Don't cry.

359
00:18:35,433 --> 00:18:36,533
It's okay.

360
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,200
I'm not mad.

361
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:42,067
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

362
00:18:42,067 --> 00:18:43,800
[SARI SOBS]

363
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:45,800
Hey.

364
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:47,900
Enough.

365
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:53,900
You being nice
makes me cry more.

366
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:58,667
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

367
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:00,600
What'll happen now, sir?

368
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:02,567
I will talk to him.

369
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:07,733
You don't have to, Martin.

370
00:19:09,767 --> 00:19:11,900
We still have Andy.

371
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:14,200
No.

372
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:17,700
This is the only time
I'll ask you for something.

373
00:19:18,533 --> 00:19:22,200
[CURIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

374
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:24,733
Trust me, even just this once.

375
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:32,567
I will make sure we choose
the right partner for Hotel 88.

376
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:39,533
[CURIOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

377
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:46,033
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

378
00:19:47,667 --> 00:19:49,900
If something bad
happens to Leon,

379
00:19:50,967 --> 00:19:52,933
it's my fault?
[SCOFFS]

380
00:19:54,167 --> 00:19:56,533
Is that what's going around
in your station?

381
00:19:58,100 --> 00:20:00,600
I knew it was Leon
I was talking to.

382
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:03,967
So, he has
Sandro's burner phone.

383
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:08,667
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

384
00:20:08,667 --> 00:20:10,667
I think he knows a lot already.

385
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:14,167
Well, he knows
I'm lying to him.

386
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:17,633
I'll have trouble
infiltrating Hotel 88 now.

387
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:21,967
Haven't you
sealed the deal yet?

388
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:24,133
Not yet.

389
00:20:24,133 --> 00:20:25,767
Because of Leon.

390
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,700
I've been able
to persuade Jade and Luna.

391
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:32,000
But Leon's going to
ruin my plans.

392
00:20:33,967 --> 00:20:35,633
What are we going to do?

393
00:20:38,033 --> 00:20:40,967
If I can't get them legally,

394
00:20:40,967 --> 00:20:42,600
I'll have to play dirty.

395
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:46,000
So, I need you to find
something we can use

396
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,167
against the Almazans.

397
00:20:48,033 --> 00:20:49,867
And not just them.

398
00:20:49,867 --> 00:20:51,800
Even against Fernandez's sons.

399
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:58,767
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

400
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:04,167
They said they're going
for Sir Ronald.

401
00:21:06,533 --> 00:21:08,500
But didn't you say
at times like this,

402
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:10,033
Leon would always
have your back?

403
00:21:10,067 --> 00:21:11,533
Yeah.

404
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:14,133
But now, he wouldn't agree
with anything I'd say.

405
00:21:16,033 --> 00:21:17,567
They must be hiding something.

406
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:20,700
That's what I think, too.

407
00:21:21,233 --> 00:21:22,733
But what could it be?

408
00:21:25,867 --> 00:21:27,000
I'll find out.

409
00:21:27,733 --> 00:21:29,567
I don't want you
to worry too much.

410
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:32,233
I'm worried more about Leon.

411
00:21:33,067 --> 00:21:35,033
I'm not worried
about the investors.

412
00:21:35,033 --> 00:21:38,000
I'm sure we're going
to get Uncle Andy

413
00:21:38,267 --> 00:21:39,967
if Sir Ronald
really isn't going through.

414
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:45,000
Based on Sari's story,
it's very unlikely.

415
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:49,033
Uncle.

416
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:50,967
Uncle, I'm really sorry.

417
00:21:50,967 --> 00:21:52,600
Please let me--

418
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:53,900
Is Sari really your girlfriend?

419
00:21:55,233 --> 00:21:56,767
No, Uncle.

420
00:21:57,800 --> 00:22:00,600
Did you pretend to be a couple
to try and impress me?

421
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:01,733
[EXHALES]

422
00:22:02,233 --> 00:22:03,267
Uncle...

423
00:22:05,867 --> 00:22:07,233
You tricked me.

424
00:22:08,633 --> 00:22:10,200
I've been
doing business for years.

425
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:12,100
I won't be fooled by...

426
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:16,800
a pathetic assistant.

427
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:19,600
It's not Sari's fault.

428
00:22:19,833 --> 00:22:20,967
I'm her boss, so--

429
00:22:21,167 --> 00:22:22,600
If she's a dignified woman,

430
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:25,800
she wouldn't let her boss
take advantage of her.

431
00:22:28,933 --> 00:22:30,700
How ignorant.

432
00:22:32,667 --> 00:22:34,633
Uncle Ronald,
that is not right.

433
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:36,967
Now you're telling me
what's right or wrong?

434
00:22:37,233 --> 00:22:39,267
I know, I made a mistake,

435
00:22:39,967 --> 00:22:42,567
but that doesn't
give you the right

436
00:22:42,567 --> 00:22:44,800
to insult people
you don't even know.

437
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,600
- [SCOFFS]
- Look.

438
00:22:46,967 --> 00:22:50,567
I'm trying to talk to you
with a partnership to consider

439
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,000
based on its potential.

440
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:54,267
And if you're
a good businessman,

441
00:22:54,667 --> 00:22:56,267
you'd know
it's a good investment.

442
00:22:56,700 --> 00:22:58,833
I'm a good businessman, Martin.

443
00:22:59,967 --> 00:23:01,300
I wouldn't be successful

444
00:23:01,300 --> 00:23:03,700
if I didn't know
how to do business.

445
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:05,633
I wouldn't have lasted
this long for decades

446
00:23:05,633 --> 00:23:07,167
if I did not value
the character

447
00:23:07,167 --> 00:23:09,033
of the people
I do business with.

448
00:23:09,033 --> 00:23:13,133
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

449
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:14,767
You were raised
by a businessman.

450
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:19,033
I'm disappointed
that you don't value

451
00:23:19,033 --> 00:23:21,633
the character
of the people around you.

452
00:23:21,633 --> 00:23:28,567
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

453
00:23:38,833 --> 00:23:41,300
<i>I want to formally
tell your family</i>

454
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:42,967
<i> that I want you
to be my girlfriend.</i>

455
00:23:42,967 --> 00:23:44,867
<i>I don't think this
is the right time.</i>

456
00:23:44,867 --> 00:23:47,833
<i>Leon and I agreed
he's the better choice.</i>

457
00:23:47,833 --> 00:23:50,000
<i> How is he the better choice
when he backed out?!</i>

458
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,400
<i> You told her?</i>

459
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,000
<i> You want us to
trust your decision</i>

460
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,900
<i>but you refuse
to tell the truth?</i>

461
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,900
<i>When the situation
at Hotel 88 worsens,</i>

462
00:23:56,933 --> 00:23:58,833
<i>they'll be forced to
partner with me.</i>

463
00:23:58,833 --> 00:24:00,367
<i> What are we looking for?</i>

464
00:24:00,367 --> 00:24:02,333
<i> Something that was
very important to Papa.</i>

465
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:04,733
<i>- Aah!
- Jade, what's wrong?!</i>

466
00:24:04,733 --> 00:24:05,700
<i> A dead body!</i>

467
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:07,333
<i>- Huh?!
- There's a dead body, Kiko!</i>
